---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Structural Burnout — Burnout Is a Design Flaw"
  description="Strategic Transformations helps executives and organizations diagnose and dismantle the structural conditions that produce burnout, attrition, and systemic exhaustion."
  section="st"
  accentColor="teal"
>

  <!-- ─── HERO ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[80vh] flex items-center overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-st-gradient"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background: radial-gradient(ellipse 70% 60% at 80% 40%, rgba(13,148,136,0.1) 0%, transparent 60%);"></div>
    <!-- Left accent bar -->
    <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-[3px] bg-teal-DEFAULT"></div>

    <div class="container-wide relative z-10 py-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <span class="st-tag mb-6 inline-flex">Strategic Transformations</span>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-5xl md:text-7xl text-light font-bold leading-tight mb-6 animate-on-scroll">
          Burnout is a<br/>
          <span class="text-teal-DEFAULT italic">Design Flaw.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-muted text-xl leading-relaxed mb-4 animate-on-scroll" style="animation-delay:0.1s">
          Your people aren't the problem. <strong class="text-light">Your structure is.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-10 animate-on-scroll" style="animation-delay:0.15s">
          Strategic Transformations is a structural burnout consultancy that helps organizations identify, name, and
          dismantle the invisible architectures burning through their most committed talent — before the cost becomes
          catastrophic.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 animate-on-scroll" style="animation-delay:0.2s">
          <a href="/structural-burnout/services" class="btn-teal">View Services & Pricing</a>
          <a href="/structural-burnout/briefing" class="btn-outline-teal">Request Executive Briefing</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── PROBLEM STATEMENT ─────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-pad bg-[#0c1525]">
    <div class="container-mid">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 animate-on-scroll">
        <span class="st-tag mb-4 inline-flex">The Real Problem</span>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl text-light">
          You've treated the symptoms long enough.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
        {[
          {
            stat: '77%',
            label: 'of workers have experienced burnout',
            detail: 'Gallup reports that nearly 4 in 5 employees experience burnout — yet most organizations still treat it as an individual problem.',
          },
          {
            stat: '2–3×',
            label: 'annual salary to replace a burned-out employee',
            detail: 'Attrition driven by structural exhaustion costs organizations exponentially more than the investments required to fix the design.',
          },
          {
            stat: '67%',
            label: 'of leaders report decision fatigue affecting quality',
            detail: 'When leaders run on empty, organizations make worse decisions — not because people are weak, but because the structure demands the impossible.',
          },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="card teal-hover text-center animate-on-scroll">
            <p class="font-heading text-5xl text-teal-DEFAULT font-bold mb-3">{item.stat}</p>
            <p class="text-light font-semibold text-sm mb-3">{item.label}</p>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.detail}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-xs text-muted mt-6 italic">
        Note: Statistics sourced from Gallup State of the Global Workplace and widely cited industry research. Verify with primary sources before formal citation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── THE UNMASK FRAMEWORK ──────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-pad relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background: radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 70% at 50% 50%, rgba(13,148,136,0.06) 0%, transparent 70%);"></div>
    <div class="container-wide relative z-10">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div class="animate-on-scroll">
          <span class="st-tag mb-5 inline-flex">The UNMASK Framework</span>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl text-light mb-6">
            A practitioner-developed<br/>diagnostic system.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The UNMASK Framework was developed through years of direct organizational practice, strategic consulting,
            and lived research at the intersection of leadership, structure, and human capacity.
          </p>
          <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
            It is not a wellness program. It is not a training module. It is a structural diagnostic and recalibration
            system — built to help organizations finally see what they've been normalized into ignoring.
          </p>
          <a href="/books/" class="btn-teal">
            Get the UNMASK Blueprint →
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 animate-on-scroll" style="animation-delay:0.15s">
          {[
            { letter: 'U', title: 'Uncover', desc: 'Surface the hidden strain patterns invisible to those inside the structure.' },
            { letter: 'N', title: 'Name', desc: 'Name the architectural conditions — not the people — creating systemic exhaustion.' },
            { letter: 'M', title: 'Map', desc: 'Map impact zones across teams, leadership layers, and systems.' },
            { letter: 'A', title: 'Align', desc: 'Align structural redesign with organizational mission and human sustainability.' },
            { letter: 'S', title: 'Sustain', desc: 'Build recalibration into the ongoing operating rhythm of the organization.' },
            { letter: 'K', title: 'Keep Watch', desc: 'Maintain vigilance through accountability structures that outlast the engagement.' },
          ].map((item) => (
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 rounded-md border border-border hover:border-teal-DEFAULT/40 transition-colors bg-surface/50">
              <span class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-teal-DEFAULT shrink-0 w-8">{item.letter}</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-heading text-light font-semibold text-sm mb-1">{item.title}</p>
                <p class="text-muted text-sm">{item.desc}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── WHO THIS IS FOR ───────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-pad bg-[#0c1525]">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 animate-on-scroll">
        <span class="st-tag mb-4 inline-flex">Audience</span>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl text-light">
          This work is for organizations<br/>ready to look at the structure.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        {[
          { icon: '🏛️', label: 'C-Suite Executives', desc: 'CEOs, CHROs, COOs navigating attrition crises and leadership fatigue.' },
          { icon: '🏢', label: 'Mid-to-Large Organizations', desc: 'Enterprises with 150–5,000+ employees experiencing systemic strain.' },
          { icon: '🎤', label: 'Conference Organizers', desc: 'Leadership, HR, DEI, and executive conferences seeking a disruptive keynote voice.' },
          { icon: '🌐', label: 'Nonprofits & Faith-Based Orgs', desc: 'Mission-driven organizations burning through their most dedicated staff.' },
          { icon: '🏫', label: 'Higher Education', desc: 'Universities and academic institutions confronting faculty and staff attrition.' },
          { icon: '💰', label: 'Impact Investors', desc: 'Investors backing scalable solutions at the intersection of leadership and systems change.' },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="card teal-hover animate-on-scroll">
            <span class="text-2xl block mb-3">{item.icon}</span>
            <p class="font-heading text-light font-semibold text-sm mb-2">{item.label}</p>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── CTA STRIP ─────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="py-16 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-navy-dark/30"></div>
    <div class="container-mid relative z-10 text-center animate-on-scroll">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl text-light mb-4">
        Ready to examine the structure?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8 max-w-lg mx-auto">
        All high-commitment engagements begin with a vetting process. This protects your investment and mine.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/structural-burnout/briefing" class="btn-teal">Request Executive Briefing →</a>
        <a href="/structural-burnout/services" class="btn-outline-teal">View All Services</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
